lu.uni.geko.weaver.add
Class SimpleAdderWrapper

java.lang.Object
  lu.uni.geko.weaver.add.SimpleAdderWrapper
All Implemented Interfaces:
MightyAdderExt
public class SimpleAdderWrapper
extends Object
implements MightyAdderExt

A default implementation of the extension point lu.uni.geko.weaver.add.mightyadderext that wraps a simple adder so that it can be used like a might adder (object adapter pattern).

See Also:
SimpleAdderExt, MightyAdderExt

addAvElementsToWovenModel

public void addAvElementsToWovenModel(Advice advice,
                                      AdviceEffectuation avffectuation,
                                      FeatureEquivalenceHelper featureEquivalenceHelper,
                                      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI wovenMURI)
Description copied from interface: MightyAdderExt
Tries to add the advice elements that have to be added during the given advice effectuation using the information from the given advice, the given feature equivalence helper and the given URI of the woven model.

Attention: The extension has to make sure that, as side-effect, the advice elements that have successfully been added are removed from the set of remaining advice elements to be added.

Specified by:
addAvElementsToWovenModel in interface MightyAdderExt
Parameters:
advice - an advice
avffectuation - an advice effectuation
featureEquivalenceHelper - a feature equivalence helper
wovenMURI - the URI of the woven model

addToContainmentIfPossible

private void addToContainmentIfPossible(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject avElementoAdd,
                                        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject baseVariantOfAvElementToAdd,
                                        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EReference containmentReference,
                                        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject possibleContainer,
                                        Set<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> avElementsAlreadyAdded,
                                        Set<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> baseVariantsOfAlreadyContainedAvElements,
                                        FeatureEquivalenceHelper featureEquivalenceHelper)
Adds the given base variant of the given advice element to the given containment reference of the given container if the reference has the right type. If the addition was successful the elements that are contained in the added element are registered in the given sets of already contained elements.

Parameters:
avElementoAdd - the advice element to add
baseVariantOfAvElementToAdd - the base variant of the given advice element
containmentReference - the containment reference to be used for the adddition
possibleContainer - the container to be used for the addition
avElementsAlreadyAdded - the set containing the advice elements that have been added
baseVariantsOfAlreadyContainedAvElements - the set containing the base variants of the advice elements that have been added
featureEquivalenceHelper - a feature equivalence helper
